Standard and Poor's said it lowered itsrating of Southdown Inc's 50 mln dlrs of sinking funddebentures to BB-plus from BBB and removed the issue fromCreditwatch.    The downgrading reflects higher debt levels from thedebt-financed repurchase of 89 mln dlrs worth of common shares,combined with a bleaker earnings outlook due to weakness in keyenergy and Southwest cement markets. Reuter&#3;